        <abstract> 
<p>Flattered by JBJ’s discussion of coral reefs [in <hi rend="italic">Voyage of H.M.S. "Fly"</hi> 1 (1847): 347–8]. CD has always thought his <hi rend="italic">Coral reefs</hi> "too bold and speculative", so he is gratified "when anyone who has had opportunities of observation does not give his verdict against it".</p> 
        </abstract>
